title: Catherine Britt - Little Wildflower
description:
Catherine Britt &#039;s album "Little Wildflower". This 12 track album was produced by Grammy-Nominated producer, Brett Beavers and 

features guest contributors Keith Urban, Tommy Emmanuel and Buddy Miller. While Britt&#039;s first two albums were traditional country 

records, her creative desire to grow professionally as an artist and a woman is evident on this album. Catherine co-wrote nine songs; 

all of which explore the conflicting emotions that come with self-doubt, being in love and living in a city filled with ever-changing 

challenges and opportunities. Throughout the album she exposes her vulnerabilities, fears, regrets and mistakes - most notably in the 

remarkably honest &#039;What I Did Last Night&#039;. She also reveals a sexiness in &#039;Little Wildflower&#039;, &#039;Lucky Girl&#039; and &#039;You&#039;re The One I Love&#039;. This 

CD is her most honest, revealing and contemporary album to date. It&#039;s an album young women will relate to and an album people of all 

ages will grow to love and appreciate. She has toured with US superstars Brooks & Dunn as well as Alan Jackson.
